1. *Džeki* je uvek bio dobar drug. (Jack has always been a good friend.)
2. Kada je video *Džekija*, Marko se nasmešio. (When he saw Jack, Marko smiled.)
3. *Džekiju* je potrebna nova jakna. (Jack needs a new jacket.)
4. Sinoć sam se provodio sa *Džekijem*. (Last night I hung out with Jack.)
5. *Džeki* je otišao na putovanje. (Jack went on a trip.)
6. Da li si video *Džekija* danas? (Did you see Jack today?)
7. *Džeki* su odigrali sjajnu partiju. (The Jacks played a great game.)
8. *Džekiju* se sviđa nova frizura. (Jack likes his new hairstyle.)
9. Upoznao sam nekog ko se zove *Džeki*. (I met someone named Jack.)
10. *Džeki* su bili glavna tema razgovora. (Jacks were the main topic of conversation.)

Note: The word "džeki" is actually an Anglicism in Serbian and is a loanword from English, referring to the name "Jack".